  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e        \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eQuick Links\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Installed Apps in Windows 11 is an updated version of Apps \u0026amp; Features in Windows 10 and the old Programs and Features tool in the Control Panel. There are many ways to open this tool, but these are the easiest.\u003c/p\u003e        \n\n\u003cp\u003eThe WinX menu, also known as the power user menu, is a quick and easy way to access system tools and settings in Windows 11. Microsoft first introduced it in Windows 8, and it has remained a handy feature ever since.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eTo open the Installed Apps tool using the WinX menu, follow these steps:\u003c/p\u003e        \u003col\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Right-click the Start button or hit \u003cstrong\u003eWindows + X\u003c/strong\u003e on your keyboard.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        From the menu that pops up, click \u003cstrong\u003eInstalled apps\u003c/strong\u003e.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Installed Apps tool will open, showing you all the apps installed on your computer.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"use-windows-search\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e2 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Use Windows Search\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/windows-search-use-guide/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003euse Windows Search\u003c/a\u003e like a personal assistant to help you find almost anything on your computer. This means you can use it to quickly open the Installed Apps tool by following these steps:\u003c/p\u003e  