ommand, follow these steps:\u003c/p\u003e        \u003col\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Press \u003cstrong\u003eWin + R\u003c/strong\u003e on your keyboard to \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/windows-open-run-command-dialog-box/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eopen the Run window\u003c/a\u003e.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Type \u003cstrong\u003ems-settings:appsfeatures\u003c/strong\u003e in the box and hit Enter.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003c/ol\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/using-run-command-to-open-installed-apps.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                                                                \n                                    \n                                                \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/using-run-command-to-open-installed-apps.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;